Similar to #29732 but should be closed with responsible reply.

# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
@angular/common/http
### Is this a regression?
Not sure.

### Description
Cannot set observe: 'response' for request method.
## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
https://stackblitz.com/angular/qlnlvogjldn?file=src%2Fapp%2Fuploader%2Fuploader.service.ts

Modify the upload method to:
```typescript
upload(file: File) {
    if (!file) { return; }
    const formData: FormData = new FormData();
    formData.append('dataset', file, file.name);
    const req = new HttpRequest('POST', 'http://localhost:666/', formData, {
      reportProgress: true, observe: 'response'
    });

    return this.http.request(req).pipe(
      map(event => this.getEventMessage(event, file)),
      tap(message => this.showProgress(message)),
      last(), // return last (completed) message to caller
      catchError(this.handleError(file))
    );
  }
```

## üî• Exception or Error
```
    ERROR in src/app/uploader/uploader.service.ts(36,7): error TS2345: Argument of type '{ reportProgress: true; observe: string;
}' is not assignable to parameter of type '{ headers?: HttpHeaders; reportProgress?: boolean; params?: HttpParams; responseType?:
"text" | "blob" | "arraybuffer" | "json"; withCredentials?: boolean; }'.
      Object literal may only specify known properties, and 'observe' does not exist in type '{ headers?: HttpHeaders; reportProgress?: boolean; params?: HttpParams; responseType?: "text" | "blob" | "arraybuffer" | "json"; withCredentials?: boolean; }'.
```

